<L>__{exterior dunharrow plateau night}
<A>__{angle on: theoden and gamling watch the retreating figures of aragorn, legolas and gimli ... rohan soldiers emerge from their tents, crestfallen to see aragorn leave. aragorn, legolas and gimli disappear into the shadows of the mountains. the rohan soldiers murmur among themselves, "what's happening?", "where's he going?"}
<C>__{gamling}
<D>__{lord aragorn!}
<C>__{rohan soldier o.s.}
<D>__{why does he leave on the eve of battle?}
<C>__{gamling}
<D>__{he leaves because there is no hope.}
<A>__{close on: theoden as he moves forward.}
<C>__{theoden}
<D>__{he leaves because he must.}
<C>__{gamling}
<D>__{too few have come. we cannot defeat the armies of mordor.}
<C>__{theoden}
<D>__{no, we cannot . . .}
<P>__{(surveying his frightened men)}
<D>__{but we will meet them in battle, nonetheless.}
